==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tut
<hw>Tut</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <def>Be still; hush;
-- an exclamation used for checking or rebuking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tut</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tut
<hw>Tut</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw. <ets>tut</ets> a point, pipe,
tube, Dan. <ets>tut</ets> a cornet.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An imperial
ensign consisting of a golden globe with a cross on it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hassock.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tutelage</ent>⟦br⟧
